In this article, it is reported that President Obama had a phone call with Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel. The President condemned the rocket fire into Israel by Hamas and other terrorist organizations in Gaza and expressed support for Israel's right to defend itself. He also expressed concern about the risk of further escalation and emphasized the need to protect civilian lives and restore calm. The President mentioned the United States' preparedness to facilitate a cessation of hostilities, including a return to the ceasefire agreement from 2012. Condolences were offered to the people of Israel for the kidnapping and murder of teenagers, including an American-Israeli citizen, and the President urged that the perpetrators be brought to justice. The leaders also discussed the situation in East Jerusalem and the West Bank, with the President welcoming the arrest of suspects in the abduction and murder of a Palestinian teenager and expressing concern for the beating and detention of an American citizen. Lastly, they discussed the P5+1 negotiations with Iran, with the President reiterating that the United States will only accept an agreement that ensures Iran's nuclear program is peaceful.